The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) is holding a media briefing following South African Airways' planned restructuring. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) held a media briefing following South African Airways' planned restructuring. SAA has informed its more than 5,000 employees that it's restructuring. It is estimated that about 944 staff will be affected. Meanwhile, the South African Cabin Crew Association (Sacca), is objecting to the manner in which SAA informed its employees of impending retrenchments. It says the airline informed employees of its intention to restructure in a media statement. 